 Culture\'s Early Roots', NULL, 'Uncover the intriguing birth of culture through the study of resonance in caves, hooves, hearts, and harps. Venture into a journey of discovery and understanding.', '2025-07-04 07:46:55', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 4, NULL, 34, NULL, 1, 42, NULL, 1, ''),
	(2995, 1042, 857, 1042, 1314, 1, 'Polyvagal Theory, deep listening and Men\'s groups', 'polyvagal-theory-deep-listening-and-mens-groups', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo row-columns-1-1 has-section-width-uk-container padding-none\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1>{%title%}</h1></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>This is a very useful podcast exploring the importance of integrating psychedelic and expanded states of awareness.&nbsp;</h2>\n<h2>Integration is often used as a general term for what happens after a deep experiential process but what does it actually mean?</h2>\n<p>﻿This is a great podcast to listen to for those attending our <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com\" target=\"_blank\">Holotropic Breathwork workshops at Melbourne Breathwork</a>&nbsp;or for anyone looking for <a href=\"http://@page/page-27\">help with integrating their psychedelic experiences</a>.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><iframe style=\"border-radius:12px\" src=\"https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/3Btf8cRomrl04rpeIqCDpY?utm_source=generator\" width=\"100%\" height=\"352\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" allow=\"autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></figure></div>\n                        </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2020-11-18 06:52:00', NULL, 0, '1', 'https://melbournebreathwork.com/resources/the-power-of-mens-groups-and-deep-listening-insights-from-polyvagal-theory', 'mens-group-listening-in-a-circle_wvbwbz', 1042, 1, 'In today\'s society, men often face unique challenges in navigating their masculinity, emotional expression, and personal growth. Fortunately, men\'s groups have emerged as empowering spaces where men can come together, share their experiences, and support each other\'s journeys. In this blog post, we will explore the importance of men\'s groups and the practice of deep listening through the lens of Polyvagal Theory—a groundbreaking framework that sheds light on our autonomic nervous system and its impact on social interactions, emotional well-being, and personal growth.', 'Polyvagal Theory & Deep Listening - Insights for Men\'s Groups', NULL, 'Explore the significance of integrating psychedelic states with our informative podcast. Ideal for those attending our Holotropic Breathwork workshops or seeking guidance on psychedelic experience integration.', '2025-07-04 07:46:55', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 4, NULL, 35, NULL, 0, 43, NULL, 1, ''),
	(2997, 1042, 857, 1042, 1314, 1, 'The role of music in Holotropic Breathwork and how it entrains the brain', 'the-role-of-music-in-holotropic-breathwork-and-how-it-entrains-the-brain', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo row-columns-1-1 has-section-width-uk-container padding-none\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1>{%title%}</h1></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>This is a very useful podcast exploring the importance of integrating psychedelic and expanded states of awareness. Integration is often used as a general term for what happens after a deep experiential process but what does it actually mean?</h2>\n<p>﻿This is a great podcast to listen to for those attending our <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com\" target=\"_blank\">Holotropic Breathwork workshops at Melbourne Breathwork</a>.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><iframe style=\"border-radius:12px\" src=\"https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/3Btf8cRomrl04rpeIqCDpY?utm_source=generator\" width=\"100%\" height=\"352\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" allow=\"autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></figure></div>\n                        </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2020-11-18 06:52:00', NULL, 0, '1', 'https://melbournebreathwork.com/resources/how-music-entrains-the-brain-and-the-power-of-music-in-holotropic-breathwork', 'DALL_E_2023-06-04_08.24.54_-_listening_to_music_and_transcendance_digital_art_otb0gq', 1042, 1, 'Music possesses an extraordinary power to transcend language and touch the deepest corners of our hearts and minds. Its ability to generate profound emotions, influence brain activity, and inspire transformative experiences is truly remarkable. Whether through joyful melodies that lift our spirits, melancholic harmonies that evoke introspection, or pulsating rhythms that ignite our bodies, music has the capacity to ignite a kaleidoscope of emotions within us. It connects us to our deepest selves, resonates with our experiences, and creates an emotional landscape that words alone often fail to capture. As we immerse ourselves in the captivating world of music, we embark on a transformative journey that impacts both our brain and our soul, elevating us to heights of profound beauty and connection.', 'Music\'s Role in Holotropic Breathwork & Brain Entrainment | Melbourne Breathwork', NULL, 'Discover the significance of music in Holotropic Breathwork and its effects on the brain. Gain insights on integrating psychedelic and expanded states of awareness from our informative podcast.', '2025-07-04 07:46:55', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 4, NULL, 37, NULL, 0, 44, NULL, 1, ''),
	(2998, 1042, 857, 1042, 1314, 1, 'The role of the sitter in Holotropic Breathwork and the notion of Unconditional Positive Regard', 'the-role-of-music-in-holotropic-breathwork-and-how-it-entrains-the-brain-mcrw', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo row-columns-1-1 padding-none has-section-width-uk-container\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-1@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1>{%title%}</h1></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><p></p></div>\n                        </div>                    <div class=\"uk-width-1-1 content-block\">\n    <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2>This is a very useful podcast exploring the importance of integrating psychedelic and expanded states of awareness. Integration is often used as a general term for what happens after a deep experiential process but what does it actually mean?</h2>\n<p>﻿This is a great podcast to listen to for those attending our <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.com\" target=\"_blank\">Holotropic Breathwork workshops at Melbourne Breathwork</a>.</p></div>\n</div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span><iframe style=\"border-radius:12px\" src=\"https://open.spotify.com/embed/episode/3Btf8cRomrl04rpeIqCDpY?utm_source=generator\" width=\"100%\" height=\"352\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"\" allow=\"autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; fullscreen; picture-in-picture\" loading=\"lazy\"></iframe></figure></div>\n                        </div></div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2020-11-18 06:52:00', NULL, 0, '1', 'https://melbournebreathwork.com/resources/what-is-the-role-of-the-sitter-in-holotropic-breathwork', 'breathers-sitting-for-eachother_ksilmt', 1042, 1, 'In Holotropic Breathwork, the role of the sitter is vital in providing support and guidance to participants as they embark on their inner journey. The sitter\'s responsibilities align closely with the concept of Unconditional Positive Regard (UPR), which emphasizes empathy, acceptance, and non-judgment.', 'Holotropic Breathwork: Understanding the Role of the Sitter and Integration', NULL, 'Explore the crucial role of the sitter in Holotropic Breathwork and the importance of integration post-deep experiential process. Listen to our podcast for insights especially for participants at Melbourne Breathwork workshops.', '2025-07-04 07:46:55', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 4, NULL, 38, NULL, 0, 45, NULL, 1, ''),
	(2999, 1042, 857, 1042, 1314, 1, 'The Shaman\'s body by Arnold Mindell', 'the-shamans-body-by-arnold-mindell', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo has-section-width-uk-container padding-none\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/shamansbodynewsh00mind_0001_ujo9lt\" data-image=\"k9e4a77unite\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1>{%title%}</h1></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com.au/Waking-Tiger-Peter-Levine/dp/155643233X/ref=asc_df_155643233X/?tag=googleshopdsk-22&amp;linkCode=df0&amp;hvadid=341792439332&amp;hvpos=&amp;hvnetw=g&amp;hvrand=12760776731712056992&amp;hvpone=&amp;hvptwo=&amp;hvqmt=&amp;hvdev=c&amp;hvdvcmdl=&amp;hvlocint=&amp;hvlocphy=9071347&amp;hvtargid=pla-436402731263&amp;psc=1\" target=\"_blank\"></a>\"The Shaman\'s Body: A New Approach to Transforming Health, Relationships, and Community\" by Arnold Mindell is a thought-provoking and insightful book that explores the process of personal transformation and its impact on our lives and the world around us.&nbsp;</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Mindell argues that process work, a holistic approach that integrates modern Western psychology with ancient wisdom traditions, can play a vital role in transforming our lives and our world.&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>﻿One of the strengths of this book is its integration of modern Western psychology with ancient wisdom traditions. Mindell draws on a wide range of sources, including contemporary neuroscience and quantum physics, to provide a holistic understanding of the body and its connection to the universe. He also provides practical techniques and exercises for using process work to heal the body, transform relationships, and create community.</p>\n<p>Another major strength of the book is its emphasis on the power of the body. Mindell argues that the body is a key source of wisdom and guidance, and that by tapping into its wisdom, we can access a deeper understanding of ourselves and the world. He also highlights the role of the body in healing, showing how physical and emotional pain can be transformed through process work.</p>\n<p>The book is also notable for its holistic approach to health and well-being. Mindell argues that process work can help us to create a more balanced and integrated way of life, connecting us to the earth, to our communities, and to the spiritual dimensions of existence. He emphasizes the importance of connection and community in the healing process, and shows how process work can help to build stronger and more meaningful relationships.</p>\n<p>In conclusion, \"The Shaman\'s Body\" is a must-read for anyone interested in exploring the power of personal transformation. Mindell\'s writing is clear, engaging, and insightful, and his approach to healing and transformation is both practical and visionary. Whether you are a mental health professional, a spiritual seeker, or someone simply looking to deepen your connection to the world, this book will provide you with new perspectives and tools for growth and healing.</p></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2020-11-18 06:52:00', NULL, 0, '1', 'https://www.thewayofthepsychonaut.com/', 'shamansbodynewsh00mind_0001_ujo9lt', 1042, 1, '\"The Shaman\'s Body: A New Approach to Transforming Health, Relationships, and Community\" by Arnold Mindell is a thought-provoking and insightful book that explores the process of personal transformation and its impact on our lives and the world around us. Mindell argues that process work, a holistic approach that integrates modern Western psychology with ancient wisdom traditions, can play a vital role in transforming our lives and our world.', 'The Shaman\'s Body by Arnold Mindell - A Guide to Transformation', NULL, 'Explore personal transformation through \'The Shaman\'s Body\' by Arnold Mindell, integrating modern psychology and ancient wisdom. Learn practical techniques for healing, transformation, and building meaningful relationships.', '2025-07-04 07:46:55', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 4, NULL, 39, NULL, 0, 46, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3000, 1042, 857, 1042, 1314, 1, 'The Silent Hike', 'the-silent-hike', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo has-section-width-uk-container padding-none row-columns-1-3_2-3\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_70/f_auto/r_0/1042/EFFD3B03-CA1A-47EE-A201-DE969030790D_lntidb\" data-image=\"t9gyedx4ngq3\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-2-3@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2 style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">The Silent Hike</h2>\n<p style=\"margin: 0px;\" data-redactor-style-cache=\"margin: 0px;\">An overnight adventure in one of the wild places of Victoria</p></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h4>A few weeks ago I had the privilege to travel to one of the most northern parts of Norway, way up in the Arctic Circle and take part in a 7 day hike and vision quest across the Tundra. It was an incredible immersion in nature, physically challenging and also deeply rewarding.</h4>\n<p>The landscape was wild, mild and silent. We experienced very long days with around 22 hours of daylight, which in itself has the potential to produce a non ordinary state of consciousness.</p>\n<p>I was travelling with a <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.us11.list-manage.com/track/click?u=6d49e879b3f66f7ff9f47ffb9&amp;id=fb4cce4aeb&amp;e=23f8895bbc\" target=\"_blank\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://melbournebreathwork.us11.list-manage.com/track/click?u%3D6d49e879b3f66f7ff9f47ffb9%26id%3Dfb4cce4aeb%26e%3D23f8895bbc&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1724380487629000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1hnQAK9q3OhLmizb-Ns_re\">Saami shaman</a> whose teachings were simple and yet profound - \"Listen to the Nature, trust in the Nature\".</p>\n<p>It\'s no secret that this is hard to do in the city and so I have resolved to continue this practice of seeking out the wild and silent places and to continue to do this in community.</p>\n<p>And as such, I am excited to announce a new offering I\'ve called <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.us11.list-manage.com/track/click?u=6d49e879b3f66f7ff9f47ffb9&amp;id=d75404a47e&amp;e=23f8895bbc\" target=\"_blank\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://melbournebreathwork.us11.list-manage.com/track/click?u%3D6d49e879b3f66f7ff9f47ffb9%26id%3Dd75404a47e%26e%3D23f8895bbc&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1724380487629000&amp;usg=AOvVaw25Y9AYRRoaSgj8stPEC05f\">The Silent Hike</a>. The first of which will be a men\'s group process involving a few listening circles with a weekend overnight hike in a wild place close to Melbourne. If you feel called to the silence and called to nature (or know someone who is) please feel free to <a href=\"https://melbournebreathwork.us11.list-manage.com/track/click?u=6d49e879b3f66f7ff9f47ffb9&amp;id=9a7a60b0a4&amp;e=23f8895bbc\" target=\"_blank\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://melbournebreathwork.us11.list-manage.com/track/click?u%3D6d49e879b3f66f7ff9f47ffb9%26id%3D9a7a60b0a4%26e%3D23f8895bbc&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1724380487629000&amp;usg=AOvVaw3SaZXmPAWHFnKOIzrtFGn9\">get in touch</a>. </p></div>\n                        </div>                        \n                                                                                            </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            \n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2024-08-22 07:14:46', NULL, 0, '1', 'https://melbournebreathwork.com/mens-groups/the-silent-hike-oct-2024', 'EFFD3B03-CA1A-47EE-A201-DE969030790D_lntidb', 1042, 1, 'A few weeks ago I had the privilege to travel to one of the most northern parts of Norway, way up in the Arctic Circle and take part in a 7 day hike and vision quest across the Tundra. It was an incredible immersion in nature, physically challenging and also deeply rewarding.', 'The Silent Hike: Wild Overnight Adventure in Victoria', NULL, 'Join The Silent Hike, an overnight adventure in Victoria\'s wild places. Experience profound immersion in nature and Saami shaman teachings. Connect with us for an unforgettable journey.', '2025-07-04 07:46:55', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 4, NULL, 40, NULL, 0, 47, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3001, 1042, 857, 1042, 1314, 1, 'Undertstanding processwork, jungian psychology and shamanism', 'undertstanding-processwork-jungian-psychology-and-shamanism', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo overlay-none padding-none has-section-width-uk-container\" style=\"background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/DALL_E_2023-05-25_11.32.05_-_existential_grief_loneliness_pain_hope_of_connection_digital_art_q6py7n\" data-image=\"k9e4a77unite\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1>Exploring Arnold Mindell\'s ProcessWork: Uniting Shamanic Practices, Jungian Psychology, and Deep Democracy</h1></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>Combining elements from various disciplines such as shamanic practices, Jungian psychology, and the concept of deep democracy, Mindell\'s approach offers a unique and holistic perspective on personal and collective transformation.&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>In this article, we will delve into the foundations of ProcessWork, its incorporation of shamanic practices, the influence of Jungian psychology, and the central tenet of deep democracy.<br></p>\n<h2>1. Understanding ProcessWork</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://melbourneprocesswork.com/psychotherapy-and-counselling\">ProcessWork</a>, also known as Process-Oriented Psychology or Worldwork, is a transdisciplinary approach to therapy and conflict resolution developed by Arnold Mindell. It seeks to understand and work with the deeper processes unfolding within individuals, relationships, and groups. The core principle of ProcessWork is that every individual or system contains a \"dreaming process\" which holds valuable information and potential for growth.</p>\n<h2>2. Shamanic Practices in ProcessWork</h2>\n<p>Mindell drew inspiration from shamanic practices found in various indigenous cultures around the world. Shamanism, a spiritual and healing tradition, emphasizes the importance of accessing altered states of consciousness and connecting with the unseen realms. In ProcessWork, shamanic practices are used to explore and engage with the symbolic language of dreams, body symptoms, and the unconscious.</p>\n<p>By incorporating shamanic techniques like trance, movement, and ritual, Mindell expanded the scope of traditional psychotherapy. These practices allow individuals to access different aspects of their psyche, communicate with unconscious elements, and gain a deeper understanding of their experiences. Shamanic practices also provide a means for individuals to connect with the collective unconscious and tap into the wisdom of ancestral knowledge.</p>\n<h2>3. Jungian Psychology and ProcessWork</h2>\n<p>Jungian psychology, developed by Carl Jung, heavily influenced Mindell\'s work. Jung proposed that the human psyche is comprised of conscious and unconscious elements, and he explored the significance of symbols, archetypes, and the collective unconscious. ProcessWork builds upon Jung\'s concepts by emphasizing the importance of working with the unconscious and the symbolic language it presents.</p>\n<p>ProcessWork utilizes Jungian concepts such as amplification (amplifying the meaning of symbols or experiences) and active imagination (engaging in dialogue with dream figures or inner characters) to gain insights into unconscious processes. The integration of Jungian psychology with shamanic practices in ProcessWork allows individuals to access and explore the rich tapestry of the psyche, facilitating personal growth and transformation.</p>\n<h2>4. Deep Democracy and ProcessWork</h2>\n<p>Central to Mindell\'s approach is the concept of deep democracy. Deep democracy refers to the recognition and inclusion of all voices and perspectives within a system, whether they are dominant or marginalized. It acknowledges that conflicts and disturbances in personal or collective realms often arise from unacknowledged or repressed aspects seeking integration.</p>\n<p>ProcessWork fosters deep democracy by creating a space for open dialogue, active listening, and amplification of marginalized voices. By valuing and exploring the different roles, viewpoints, and experiences within a system, ProcessWork aims to uncover the underlying dynamics, facilitate conflict resolution, and promote transformation.</p>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>Arnold Mindell\'s ProcessWork has emerged as a transformative and integrative approach to psychology, drawing from shamanic practices, Jungian psychology, and the concept of deep democracy. By incorporating shamanic techniques, ProcessWork offers individuals a means to connect with the unconscious, engage with symbolism, and access deeper layers of personal and collective experience.</p>\n<p>Moreover, the influence of Jungian psychology provides a framework for understanding and working with the unconscious and the symbolic language it presents. Finally, the concept of deep democracy emphasizes the importance of</p>\n<p> inclusivity, dialogue, and valuing diverse perspectives, enabling ProcessWork to address conflicts and promote personal and collective growth.</p>\n<p>As Mindell continues to refine and expand upon his work, ProcessWork offers a valuable and holistic approach for individuals, therapists, and communities to explore the depths of the human psyche, foster dialogue, and facilitate transformative change.</p></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2020-11-18 06:52:00', NULL, 0, '1', 'https://www.thewayofthepsychonaut.com/', 'DALL_E_2023-05-25_11.32.05_-_existential_grief_loneliness_pain_hope_of_connection_digital_art_q6py7n', 1042, 1, 'Arnold Mindell is a renowned psychotherapist, author, and teacher who has made significant contributions to the field of psychology through his development of ProcessWork. Combining elements from various disciplines such as shamanic practices, Jungian psychology, and the concept of deep democracy, Mindell\'s approach offers a unique and holistic perspective on personal and collective transformation. In this article, we will delve into the foundations of ProcessWork, its incorporation of shamanic practices, the influence of Jungian psychology, and the central tenet of deep democracy.', 'Exploring ProcessWork: A Blend of Shamanism, Jungian Psychology & Deep Democracy', NULL, 'Dive into Arnold Mindell\'s ProcessWork, a unique approach combining shamanic practices, Jungian psychology, and deep democracy. Discover its role in personal and collective transformation, and how it can help you tap into the wisdom of ancestral knowledge.', '2025-07-04 07:46:55', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 4, NULL, 41, NULL, 0, 48, NULL, 0, ''),
	(3002, 1042, 857, 1042, 1314, 1, 'Waking the Tiger: Healing Trauma', 'way-of-the-psychonaut-stan-grof-bc0m', '<div class=\"content-row uk-position-relative uk-flex with-redo overlay-none has-section-width-uk-container padding-none\" style=\"background-color: rgb(250, 250, 250);\">\n    <div class=\"uk-container\">\n        <div class=\"uk-grid\">\n            <div class=\"uk-width-1-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><figure class=\"uk-margin-remove-top uk-position-relative redactor-component-active\" tabindex=\"-1\"><span class=\"redactor-component-caret\">﻿</span>\n                                    <img class=\"fb-image-white-border-large\" src=\"https://res.cloudinary.com/feelbettr/image/upload/q_72/f_auto//w_400/1042/waking-tiger-peter-levine_io1se4\" data-image=\"k9e4a77unite\" alt=\"\">\n                                </figure></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"uk-width-3-4@m uk-position-relative\">\n                <div class=\"grid-inner\">\n                    <div class=\"uk-sortable\">\n                                                                        <div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h1>{%title%}</h1></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h2><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com.au/Waking-Tiger-Peter-Levine/dp/155643233X/ref=asc_df_155643233X/?tag=googleshopdsk-22&amp;linkCode=df0&amp;hvadid=341792439332&amp;hvpos=&amp;hvnetw=g&amp;hvrand=12760776731712056992&amp;hvpone=&amp;hvptwo=&amp;hvqmt=&amp;hvdev=c&amp;hvdvcmdl=&amp;hvlocint=&amp;hvlocphy=9071347&amp;hvtargid=pla-436402731263&amp;psc=1\" target=\"_blank\">\"Waking the Tiger: Healing Trauma\"</a> by Peter Levine is a groundbreaking book that provides a new perspective on the nature of trauma and its effects on the body and mind. Levine explores the connection between trauma and the body\'s natural \"fight or flight\" response, and shows how this response can become stuck, leading to chronic symptoms of trauma.</h2></div>\n                        </div><div class=\"content-block\">\n                            <div class=\"content-block-inner\"><h3>One of the strengths of this book is its emphasis on the body-mind connection. Levine draws on extensive research in neuroscience and biology to show how trauma can impact not only our mental and emotional well-being, but also our physical health.&nbsp;</h3>\n<p>The book also includes practical exercises and techniques for healing trauma, such as Somatic Experiencing, which helps people release trapped energy from the body and restore balance to their nervous system.</p>\n<p>One of the key insights of the book is that trauma is not simply a psychological or emotional issue, but is deeply rooted in the body\'s natural response to stress. Levine argues that traditional talk therapy and medication-based approaches to treating trauma often fail because they do not address the underlying physiological factors.</p>\n<p>Another major strength of the book is its approach to trauma. Levine is committed to empowering individuals to take control of their own healing process, and the techniques he outlines are designed to be simple and accessible. He also emphasizes the importance of connection and community in the healing process, highlighting the role of relationships, community, and nature in restoring balance and well-being.</p>\n<p>In conclusion, \"Waking the Tiger: Healing Trauma\" is a must-read for anyone interested in understanding and healing from trauma. Levine\'s approach is unique, insightful, and empowering, and his writing style is engaging and accessible. Whether you are a mental health professional or someone who has experienced trauma, this book will provide you with practical strategies for healing and growth.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com.au/Waking-Tiger-Peter-Levine/dp/155643233X/ref=asc_df_155643233X/?tag=googleshopdsk-22&amp;linkCode=df0&amp;hvadid=341792439332&amp;hvpos=&amp;hvnetw=g&amp;hvrand=12760776731712056992&amp;hvpone=&amp;hvptwo=&amp;hvqmt=&amp;hvdev=c&amp;hvdvcmdl=&amp;hvlocint=&amp;hvlocphy=9071347&amp;hvtargid=pla-436402731263&amp;psc=1\" target=\"_blank\">Get a copy of the book on Amazon</a>﻿<br>﻿</p></div>\n                        </div>                    </div>\n                </div>\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"content-row-overlay\"></div>\n</div>', '2020-11-18 06:52:00', NULL, 0, '1', 'https://www.thewayofthepsychonaut.com/', 'waking-tiger-peter-levine_io1se4', 1042, 1, '\"Waking the Tiger: Healing Trauma\" by Peter Levine is a groundbreaking book that provides a new perspective on the nature of trauma and its effects on the body and mind. Levine explores the connection between trauma and the body\'s natural \"fight or flight\" response, and shows how this response can become stuck, leading to chronic symptoms of trauma.', 'Waking the Tiger: Healing Trauma - A Groundbreaking Book by Peter Levine', NULL, 'Explore \'Waking the Tiger: Healing Trauma\' by Peter Levine, a revolutionary look into trauma\'s impact on body and mind. Discover unique insights, practical healing techniques, and the importance of community in the healing journey.', '2025-07-04 07:46:55', '2026-01-05 00:10:30', 4, NULL, 42, NULL, 0, 49, NULL, 0, ''),
